    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Rigshospitalet, Denmark</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose is to evaluate,in 20 patients, if the sentinel node(s) in melanoma can be
      detected by lymph contrast ultrasound. In comparing the patients will also get
      lymph-scintigraphy and sentinel node detection wiht blue dye.

      The goal is to improve the method for detecting sentinel node(s) in melanoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
